Package org.odpi.openmetadata.adapters.connectors.productmanager.productcatalog

Class ProductDefinitionBean

java.lang.Object
org.odpi.openmetadata.adapters.connectors.productmanager.productcatalog.ProductDefinitionBean
All Implemented Interfaces:
ProductDefinition
public class ProductDefinitionBean extends Object implements ProductDefinition
The ProductDefinition describes the products (or templates for products) found in the open metadata product catalog.

  • Constructor Details

    • ProductDefinitionBean

      public ProductDefinitionBean(String typeName, ProductDefinition[] productGroups, String productName, String identifier, ProductFolderDefinition parent, String displayName, String description, String category, ProductGovernanceDefinition license, ProductCommunityDefinition community, ProductSubscriptionDefinition[] subscriptionTypes, String dataSpecTableName, ProductDataFieldDefinition[] dataSpecIdentifiers, ProductDataFieldDefinition[] dataSpecFields, String assetTypeName, String assetIdentifier, ConnectorProvider connectorProvider, Map<String,Object> configurationProperties, String catalogTargetName)
      Construct a product definition.
      Parameters:
      typeName - name of the type to use - eg DigitalProduct or DigitalProductFamily
      productGroups - list of groups that this product belongs to (can be null)
      productName - name of the product
      identifier - product identifier
      parent - folder/product group
      displayName - display name
      description - description
      category - category of product
      license - license
      community - community
      subscriptionTypes - list of subscription types offered
      dataSpecTableName - logical name of the tabular data set
      dataSpecIdentifiers - list of data fields that form the unique identifier
      dataSpecFields - list of other data fields
      assetTypeName - type name for the associated product asset
      assetIdentifier - identifier for the appropriate asset
      connectorProvider - connector provider class (or null)
      configurationProperties - configuration properties for the asset's connection
      catalogTargetName - catalog target name for the refresh process
